faunalytics 0.1.0
  • Reference

    Fish beliefs data set, abridged

    test_data.Rd

    A dataset containing survey results from Canadian participants who were asked to report their beliefs about fishes and if they would pledge to reduce their fish consumption

    Format

    A data frame with 576 rows and variables:

    date

    date of survey completion

    speed

    number of seconds taken to complete survey

    gender

    gender selected by participant

    gender_write_in

    additional gender write-in information

    gender_group

    grouped gender data

    race_ethnicity

    race selected by participant

    race_ethnicity_write_in

    additional race write-in information

    age

    participant age

    income

    income range selected by participant

    education

    education selected by participant

    latinx

    Latinx ethnicity identifier

    belief_1

    level of agreement: "Fish can learn"

    belief_2

    level of agreement: "Fish don't mind being in a barren environment"

    belief_3

    level of agreement: "Fish don't care about being over-crowded"

    belief_4

    level of agreement: "Fish never find it stressful to be picked up or handled"

    ffq_1

    Frequency of consumption: Dairy

    ffq_2

    Frequency of consumption: Chicken

    ffq_3

    Frequency of consumption: Turkey

    ffq_4

    Frequency of consumption: Fish and seafood

    ffq_5

    Frequency of consumption: Pork

    ffq_6

    Frequency of consumption: Beef

    ffq_7

    Frequency of consumption: Other meat

    ffq_8

    Frequency of consumption: Eggs

    outcome

    pledged to reduce consumption of fish products

    Source

    https://osf.io/n452j/
